  id: Cleidobrachial_muscle_Clavicular_part_of_deltoid.R
  partName: Cleidobrachial muscle Clavicular part of deltoid Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right cleidobrachial muscle, forming part of the canine deltoid complex,
    connects the clavicular region to the upper forelimb. Its primary function is
    to flex the shoulder and advance the limb during movement. This muscle contributes
    significantly to coordinated forelimb mechanics, allowing efficient stride formation
    and controlled shoulder positioning.
  - During activities such as running, turning, and climbing, the cleidobrachial
    muscle works alongside surrounding shoulder muscles to maintain stability and
    balanced motion. It also assists in absorbing mechanical stress placed on the
    shoulder joint during locomotion.
